name: TheAtlantic
text: Key Democrats from the Biden and Sanders wings of the party are backing Jaime Harrison to chair the Democratic National Committee, @isaacdovere reports: https://t.co/W6rlTn8OLf

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @IsaacDovere: NEW from me: the pieces are coming together quickly for @harrisonjaime to be the new DNC chair, including @WhipClyburn who says "all of Biden’s friends know what I feel about it.”

https://t.co/0WzlFyTpOm

name: TheAtlantic
text:
House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy suggested Tuesday that Joe Biden might not be the next president.

In June, @anneapplebaum asked why some Republican leaders have chosen to be complicit with President DonaldTrump’s immoral and dangerous acts. https://t.co/GCrxyNrOKR

name: TheAtlantic
text: "The 2020 electoral outcome—Democratic White House, Republican Senate—was the worst one in terms of getting anything done in the Capitol, and is thus a pending disaster for the country’s sick, unemployed, and poor," @AnnieLowrey writes: https://t.co/IaTJlA4MK5

name: TheAtlantic
text: "A responsible commander in chief would be underscoring the stability and strength of U.S. defense and intelligence agencies during the presidential transition. But that’s not the commander in chief we have," @KoriSchake writes: https://t.co/mtoHz3uYE6
